My first big concert as a kid was in 1983:  Men at Work with a fairly unknown Blues Guitarist by the name of Stevie Ray Vaughan as the opener, at the late great Mercer Arena.  Here’s a clip of I-5 in 1983, with scenes from Southcenter to Northgate Mall, courtesy of a YouTube page called Highway Videos ⬅️It’s the closest thing to a Time Machine.

The current #SoundTransit light rail line.  I attended Van Asselt, Wing Luke, Dunlap & South Shore schools (respectively) through the 70s, which reside evenly on both sides of Empire.  Needless to say, this run similar to this view is my hard-written imprint of the world before it grew beyond the Valley.  Courtesy of a YouTube page called Highway Videos ⬅️It’s the closest thing to a Time Machine. Inspired by this week’s fantastic fantastic #feliksbanel @mynorthwest  story covering Susanna Ryan’s /  @seattlewalkreport  research on Seattle’s Old Tile Street Markers.  I recalled this clip, courtesy of @seattlecityarchives, moving images item number 33 from 1971, showing the placement of Aurora’s hidden line trays.  Enjoy.  #old99 #seattleinthe70s #auroraave #seattle

Moved from South Seattle to North Everett almost overnight in the early 80s.  In ‘83, before the CT, the only convenient ride to 8th & Stewart a $3.40 Greyhound ticket.  Otherwise I was here, on my 10-speed.  Song choice is not a favorite, but a filler that possessed the airwaves between all other songs in the summer of ‘83.  #iykyk Courtesy of a YouTube page called Highway Videos ⬅️It’s the closest thing to a Time Machine. Most will agree, that stretch of 167 through town hasn’t changed a stitch since this clip, 41 years ago.  The SR 167 Completion Project in Pierce County is Expected to be completed in 2029.  Curious to know how that area will flourish once the highway is complete.  Clip is courtesy of a YouTube page called, Highway Videos. ⬅️Link in bio. #puyallup #sumner #miltonwa #piercecounty #southkingcounty #seattlesuburbs #SR167
